  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Buidler CLI stores global (user level) config in the users `$HOME` directory (`~/.buidler/config.json`).\r\n\r\nI would propose that the config file be moved as [per the XDG basedir specification](https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html). To ensure backwards compatibility, the config file should be sourced:\r\n\r\n- From `$HOME/.buidler/config.json`, if the file exists\r\n- From `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME\\buidler\\config.json`, if the env variable is set\r\n- From `$HOME\\.config\\buidler\\config.json` otherwise.\r\n\r\nThis follows the spec (keeps the user homedir clean) and retains backward compatibility.\r\n\r\nBear in mind that this does not solve compatibility with Windows.",
